{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.7",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 7,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 7 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:1",
      "text": "My son, keep my words and treasure up my commandments with you;",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:2",
      "text": "keep my commandments and live, keep my teachings as the apple of your eye;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:3",
      "text": "bind them on your fingers, write them on the tablet of your heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:4",
      "text": "Say to wisdom, “You are my sister,” and call insight your intimate friend;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:5",
      "text": "to preserve you from the loose woman, from the adventuress with her smooth words.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:6",
      "text": "For at the window of my house I have looked out through my lattice,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:7",
      "text": "and I have seen among the simple, I have perceived among the youths, a young man without sense,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:8",
      "text": "passing along the street near her corner, taking the road to her house",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:9",
      "text": "in the twilight, in the evening, at the time of night and darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:10",
      "text": "And lo, a woman meets him, dressed as a harlot, wily of heart.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:11",
      "text": "She is loud and wayward, her feet do not stay at home;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:12",
      "text": "now in the street, now in the market, and at every corner she lies in wait.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:13",
      "text": "She seizes him and kisses him, and with impudent face she says to him:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:14",
      "text": "“I had to offer sacrifices, and today I have paid my vows;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:15",
      "text": "so now I have come out to meet you, to seek you eagerly, and I have found you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:16",
      "text": "I have decked my couch with coverings, colored spreads of Egyptian linen;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:17",
      "text": "I have perfumed my bed with myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:18",
      "text": "Come, let us take our fill of love till morning; let us delight ourselves with love.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:19",
      "text": "For my husband is not at home; he has gone on a long journey;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:20",
      "text": "he took a bag of money with him; at full moon he will come home.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:21",
      "text": "With much seductive speech she persuades him; with her smooth talk she compels him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:22",
      "text": "All at once he follows her, as an ox goes to the slaughter, or as a stag is caught fast",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.23",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:23",
      "text": "till an arrow pierces its entrails; as a bird rushes into a snare; he does not know that it will cost him his life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.24",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:24",
      "text": "And now, O sons, listen to me, and be attentive to the words of my mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.25",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:25",
      "text": "Let not your heart turn aside to her ways, do not stray into her paths;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.26",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:26",
      "text": "for many a victim has she laid low; yea, all her slain are a mighty host.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.7.27",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 7,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 7:27",
      "text": "Her house is the way to Sheol, going down to the chambers of death.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
